On Wed, Jan 27, 1999 at 06:50:05AM -0800, Ron Forrester mentioned:
> 
> Someone reported the other day seeing a lot of interrupts's/sec when
> playing sound. 
> 
> With 2.2.0-final installed, my system seems much busier than it I would
> think when playing MP3's using x11amp (against the OSS AWE drivers). 
> 
> I would like to check the interrupts per second, how can I do this? Is
> it something in /proc? Or a tool I can get?
 There is a dockable applet called "wmint" that could be useful. It's off
the WindowMaker page (www.windowmaker.org). It reads directly from
/proc/interrupts.
